The paper discusses the design and implementation of a static analyzer for safety-critical software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of abstract interpretation, which is a technique used in programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper specifically focuses on safety-critical software, which suggests the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the static analyzer to safety-critical embedded software, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
